The paper proposes a natural language interface to a graph-based bibliographic information retrieval system, which involves techniques such as tokenization, named entity recognition, and syntactic analysis. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Deep Learning (cs.DL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories of arXiv CS.
